# MAAS Operations Patterns

## Machine State Transitions

- Failed commissioning → mark_broken → mark_fixed → Ready → commission
- Failed to enter rescue mode → mark_broken → mark_fixed → Ready
- Deployed → release → Ready → commission
- MAAS 3.3 at some sites returns 409 on PUT in various states — use mark_broken/mark_fixed cycle

## Power Type Configuration

- GPU nodes (Supermicro AS-8125GS): IPMI with LAN_2_0, cipher_suite_id=3, efi boot
- CPU nodes (Supermicro SYS-121H-TNR): Same IPMI config, but BMC firmware differs
- When changing power_type or privilege_level, use direct MAAS API PUT (OAuth1Session)
- The `maas_set_machine_power_parameters` MCP tool only handles power_address, power_user, power_pass

## Commissioning Troubleshooting

- "BMC never transitioned from X to Y": Usually hardware issue, not auth
- "Access denied while performing power action": Privilege level mismatch or account locked
- "Incorrect password": Wrong credentials in MAAS power_parameters
- Commissioning timeout (30min) with no PXE events: NIC MAC mismatch or wrong boot NIC
- Check BIOS BootOptions MACs vs MAAS interface MACs when PXE fails

## AWX Integration

- AWX inventories are organized by NetBox cluster → hostname
- Machines must be assigned to a NetBox cluster to appear in AWX inventories
- Released machines (cluster=null) won't be in any AWX inventory
- Use workflow templates (e.g. "0 - Workflows / Acceptance Test") not individual job templates
- Workflow may require inventory_id on launch, not limit
